@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor white
scale 2

title Activity Diagram: View Tyre Stints

|User|
start
:Request Tyre Stint visualization;

|System|
:Retrieve selected drivers;
:Fetch stint data for each driver\nfrom FastF1 API;

if (Stint data available?) then (yes)
  :Parse stint information\n(start lap, end lap, compound);
  :Map tyre compounds to colors\n(Soft=Red, Medium=Yellow, Hard=White);
  :Generate stint visualization\n(horizontal bar chart);
  :Render visualization on screen;

  |User|
  :Analyze tyre strategies;
  :Compare pit stop timing\nand compound choices;

else (no)
  :Display error message\n"Stint data not available\nfor selected drivers";
endif

stop

@enduml

' ============================================================
' ACTIVITY DIAGRAM TEXT DESCRIPTION
' ============================================================
' Use Case: View Tyre Stints
'
' Step 1: The User requests the Tyre Stint visualization.
' Step 2: The System retrieves the list of selected drivers.
' Step 3: The System fetches stint data for each selected
'         driver from the FastF1 API.
' Step 4: The System checks if stint data is available.
'         - If NO: Display an error message indicating
'           stint data is not available.
'         - If YES: Proceed to Step 5.
' Step 5: The System parses the stint information including
'         start lap, end lap, and tyre compound used.
' Step 6: The System maps tyre compounds to their standard
'         colors (Soft=Red, Medium=Yellow, Hard=White).
' Step 7: The System generates a horizontal bar chart
'         visualizing the stint strategy for each driver.
' Step 8: The System renders the visualization on screen.
' Step 9: The User analyzes tyre strategies and compares
'         pit stop timing and compound choices between
'         the selected drivers.
' ============================================================
